	<tr valign=top>
	<td class="bodycopy">
		<!--ANSWERS BEGINS HERE-->
<b>What about retreat and adjustment phases?  Do I make offers to
units during those phases of the game too?</b><br>
	No.  All of a player's retreat, build, and remove orders are under the
	control of that individual player acting alone.  In these phases,
	a Payola game is  just like a standard Diplomacy game.
	Just as you enter your movement phase offers at the Website,
	you can issue your retreat and adjustment phase orders here too.

<P><b>
When are orders adjudicated? Will moves process before the deadline if
all players have submitted their offers?
</b><br>
	The short answer to the second question
	is, "Yes; assuming no player has set his <i>wait flag</i>."
	The complete answer to this and other similar questions can be found on the
	Webpage that answers the
	<a href=<URL>?page=Questions>Common Questions About the DPjudge</a>.  The
	complete processing mechanics is described there.  Simply
	remember to read "offer sheets" when it talks about "movement orders".
		<!--ANSWERS ENDS HERE-->
	</td>
	</tr>
