	<tr valign=top>
	<td class="bodycopy">
		<!--ANSWERS BEGINS HERE-->
		<b>What if a unit doesn't receive any offer at all?
What will it do?</b><br>
	It will <tt>HOLD</tt>.  This is because if a player offers no
	non-negative offer to one of his own units, a default offer for that unit
	to <tt>HOLD</tt> --
	offering to pay zero "silver pieces" -- is automatically entered for him
	at the end of his list of offers.

<P><b>What if the only offer a unit gets is a "negative" offer?  What will the unit do?</b><br>
	Again, it will <tt>HOLD</tt>.
	This is explained as follows:  each negative offer that does not ask
	for the unit to <tt>HOLD</tt> "comes with" a
	"hidden" direct offer to pay zero silver pieces if the unit is
	ordered to <tt>HOLD</tt>, and it is this offer -- the only positive
	("do this") offer that the unit gets -- which is followed.
	<P>
	Ah, you say, but what if the offer
	is one that asks for the unit <i>not</i> to <tt>HOLD</tt>?  As in
	<ul><dd><tt>4 ! A PAR H</tt></dd></ul>
	It doesn't matter.  The unit will still <tt>HOLD</tt> (the bribing
	player will <i>not</i> be charged four silver pieces, however).  The
	offer that will be accepted is the owning player's default (automatically
	created) zero silver piece offer <tt>HOLD</tt> offer.
	<P>
	The thing to remember about negative offers is that they never give a
	unit an order that it can consider.  Units <i>only</i> look at the
	<i>non-</i>negative offers made to them when deciding what order to follow.
	Money that is offered in a negative offer is <i>added</i> as appropriate,
	to each non-negative offer that fits its requirements, of course, but
	there must be some non-negative offer to catch the money or it essentially
	goes unoffered.  The lesson is that if you ever offer a unit money
	<i>not</i> to <tt>HOLD</tt>, be sure to make it a "direct" offer
	as well, just in case your money has nothing to which it can be added.

<P><b>Wait a minute.  In the rules it says that a player
cannot offer a zero silver piece offer to any unit that he doesn't own.  But,
in the answer to that last question, you said that a zero silver piece
offer for a unit to <tt>HOLD</tt> is automatically paired with every single
negative offer.  What gives?</b><br>
	The restriction against zero silver piece offers to foreign units is real,
	but it applies only to offers actually written by a player.
	The zero silver piece offer to <tt>HOLD</tt> which is added automatically
	is exempt from this prohibition.
