		<b>Can I set a bookmark (fans of Bill Gates: a "favorite")
that will get me straight to my Payola game?</b><br>
	Yes.  Paste the following lines together into a single line, with
	no included whitespace, and there you have it:<br><tt>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		http://www.floc.net/dpjudge?<br>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		game=<font color=red><i>gameName</i></font>&<br>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		power=<font color=red><i>powerName</i></font>&<br>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		password=<font color=red><i>yourPassword</i></font></tt>
<P><b>How do I change my password at the Payola Place 
Website?</b><br>
	You must use the e-mail interface to do this (sending a
	<tt>SET&nbsp;ADDRESS</tt> or <tt>SET&nbsp;PASSWORD</tt> command).
	See <a href=<URL>?page=Email#8>the details on these commands</a>
	in the <a href=<URL>?page=Email>questions about the DPjudge
	e-mail interface</a>.
	<P>
	If your game is running on a Ken Lowe judge, using the DPjudge as a
	Web front-end,
	your Payola Place password <i>must</i> match your password on the Ken Lowe
	judge computer that is running the game.  So if you ever change your
	password for the game on the judge, you should be <i>sure</i> to have
	your Payola Place password changed <i>immediately</i>.
<P><b>Where can I get a PostScript viewer so that I can
	see the "Season By Season" Maps?</b><br>
	At the <a href=http://www.cs.wisc.edu/~ghost>Ghostscript, Ghostview,
	and GSview</a> site.  You need ghostscript (which is called <tt>gs</tt>
	if you need it for a Personal Computer) <b><u>and</u></b> ghostview
	(<tt>gsview32</tt> for the PC).  Downloading and installing ghostview
	(<tt>gsview32</tt>) should drag ghostscript along with it and set you
	all up.  It should even tell your Web browser to use gsview to view
	PostScript files (if it doesn't, you can teach your Web browser to
	do so yourself).  Note that you will want to set the "Orientation"
	in ghostview to "Seascape" to show the map right-side-up.

<P><b>So there's an e-mail interface I can use to submit
my offers and orders and send my press messages?  What do I need to
know?</b><br>
	Yes, you can submit your offers and your retreat and adjustment
	orders by e-mail -- just include them somewhere under your <tt>SIGNON</tt>
	(and outside of a press message!)
	Speaking of press, yes, in addition to being able to compose and send
	press from the Website, you can also
	send it from your favorite e-mail application.  Everything
	you need to know about how to do all this is in the
	<a href=<URL>?page=Email>E-Mail Interface Question
	and Answer List</a>.
